<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>LE Handoff Package — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Strictly Private &amp; Confidential</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Investigative Findings &amp; Recommended Actions</div>
    <h1>Law Enforcement<br/>Handoff Package</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Independent on-chain trace and identified-wallet record prepared for
      handoff to the assigned investigator or supervising agency.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared On Behalf Of</dt>
      <dd>{{ victim.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ victim.citizenship or "Citizenship not on record" }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared By</dt>
      <dd>{{ investigator.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>{{ investigator.email }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Number</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Brief Identifier</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ brief_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Stolen Value (Initial)</dt>
      <dd>USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }}<span class="secondary">{{ asset.symbol }} on {{ primary_chain | default("Ethereum") }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Asset Issuer</dt>
      <dd>{{ issuer.name }}{% if issuer.jurisdiction %}<span class="secondary">{{ issuer.jurisdiction }}</span>{% endif %}</dd>
    </div>
    {% if issuer_freezable %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Recoverable Position</dt>
      <dd>{{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }}<span class="secondary">{{ issuer_freezable.token }} at {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }} {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "wallets" }} ({{ issuer_freezable.freeze_capability }} freeze capability)</span></dd>
    </div>
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Additional Under Review</dt>
      <dd>{{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_suspected }}<span class="secondary">incl. {{ issuer_freezable.investigate_count }} wallets pending KYC verification</span></dd>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    {% endif %}
  </dl>
</section>

<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
<div class="summary-box">
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.7em 0;">
    On {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC, {{ asset.amount_human }}
    {{ asset.symbol }} (USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }} at the time of
    transaction) was removed without authorization from
    {{ victim.name }}'s wallet
    {% if victim.citizenship %}(citizen of {{ victim.citizenship }}){% endif %}.
    The token is issued by {{ issuer.name }}{% if issuer.jurisdiction %},
    a {{ issuer.jurisdiction }} entity{% endif %}.
    {% if issuer.secondary_party %}
    Its underlying strategy is operated by {{ issuer.secondary_party }}
    ({{ issuer.secondary_role }}).
    {% endif %}
  </p>
  {% if issuer_freezable %}
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.7em 0;">
    The position was forwarded by the perpetrator through a chain of
    intermediate wallets and converted into
    <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.token }}</strong>, the stablecoin
    issued by {{ issuer.name }}. As of {{ verified_at }} UTC,
    <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }}</strong>
    of stolen funds is held in {{ issuer_freezable.token }} at
    {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }}
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority — these
    positions are flagged FREEZABLE in section 4.1.
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
    An additional
    {{ issuer_freezable.investigate_count }}
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.investigate_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    holding {{ issuer_freezable.token }} are flagged INVESTIGATE,
    representing
    {{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_suspected }}
    in further funds pending KYC verification at {{ issuer.short_name }}.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0;">
    {{ issuer.short_name }}'s protocol-level controls over
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} are the available mechanism for
    pausing redemption of the recoverable positions. We recommend
    that a preservation request be issued to {{ issuer.short_name }}
    as a matter of priority, citing the addresses listed in
    section 5 of this package.
  </p>
  {% else %}
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.7em 0;">
    The position was promptly forwarded by the perpetrator to a secondary
    wallet at <a class="mono" href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">{{ current_holder.address }}</a>, where
    {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound transfers have been
    observed as of {{ verified_at }} UTC.
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0;">
    The asset's issuer-level controls remain the only available
    mechanism by which redemption can be paused. We recommend that
    a preservation request be issued to {{ issuer.short_name }} as a
    matter of priority.
  </p>
  {% endif %}
</div>

<h2>2. Victim Information</h2>
<dl class="meta-grid">
  <dt>Full name:</dt>           <dd>{{ victim.name }}</dd>
  {% if victim.citizenship %}<dt>Citizenship:</dt><dd>{{ victim.citizenship }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.address %}<dt>Residential address:</dt><dd>{{ victim.address }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.email %}<dt>Email:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.email }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.phone %}<dt>Phone:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.phone }}</dd>{% endif %}
  <dt>Affected wallet:</dt>     <dd><a class="mono" href="{{ victim_wallet_explorer_url }}">{{ victim.wallet_address }}</a></dd>
  {% if victim.legal_counsel %}
  <dt>Legal counsel:</dt><dd>{{ victim.legal_counsel }}{% if victim.legal_counsel_email %} &lt;{{ victim.legal_counsel_email }}&gt;{% endif %}</dd>
  {% endif %}
</dl>

{% if victim.incident_summary %}
<h3>Victim's account of the incident</h3>
<p>{{ victim.incident_summary }}</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>3. Timeline of Events (UTC)</h2>
<div class="timeline">
  <div class="timeline-event theft">
    <time>{{ theft_event.timestamp_human }}</time> &nbsp;—&nbsp;
    <strong>Initial theft.</strong> {{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }} transferred
    from victim wallet <a class="mono" href="{{ theft_event.from_explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.from_address }}</a>
    to perpetrator wallet <a class="mono" href="{{ theft_event.to_explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.to_address }}</a>.
    Tx: <span class="mono"><a href="{{ theft_event.explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.tx_hash }}</a></span>
  </div>
  {% for hop in hops %}
  <div class="timeline-event transfer">
    <time>{{ hop.timestamp_human }}</time> &nbsp;—&nbsp;
    <strong>Hop {{ loop.index }}.</strong>
    {{ hop.amount_human }} {{ hop.symbol }} transferred from
    <a class="mono" href="{{ hop.from_explorer_url }}">{{ hop.from_address }}</a>
    to <a class="mono" href="{{ hop.to_explorer_url }}">{{ hop.to_address }}</a>.
    Tx: <span class="mono"><a href="{{ hop.explorer_url }}">{{ hop.tx_hash }}</a></span>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
  <div class="timeline-event current">
    <time>{{ verified_at }}</time> &nbsp;—&nbsp;
    {% if issuer_freezable %}
    <strong>Current state.</strong> Recoverable funds totaling
    {{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }} held as
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} across
    {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }}
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
    (plus {{ issuer_freezable.investigate_count }} additional
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} positions under KYC verification).
    {% else %}.{% endif %}
    Specific addresses enumerated in section 5.
    {% else %}
    <strong>Current state.</strong> Position remains in
    <a class="mono" href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">{{ current_holder.address }}</a>.
    {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound transfers of the stolen asset observed
    since receipt.
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</div>

{% if flow_filename %}
<h2>3.1 Fund Flow Diagram</h2>
<p class="attachment-note">
  The fund-flow diagram is provided as a separate SVG attachment
  (<span class="mono">{{ flow_filename }}</span>) accompanying this
  package. Open in any modern browser for full-resolution inspection;
  each wallet node links to its Etherscan record. Solid arrows
  represent observed on-chain transfers, with edge labels showing
  USD-denominated value at the time of transfer and line thickness
  scaled logarithmically to value.
</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>4. Stolen Asset Details</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr><th>Asset symbol</th>           <td>{{ asset.symbol }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Token contract address</th> <td>{% if asset_contract_explorer_url %}<a class="mono" href="{{ asset_contract_explorer_url }}">{{ asset.contract }}</a>{% else %}<span class="mono">{{ asset.contract }}</span>{% endif %}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Issuer (legal entity)</th>  <td>{{ asset.issuer }}</td></tr>
  {% if issuer.jurisdiction %}<tr><th>Issuer jurisdiction</th><td>{{ issuer.jurisdiction }}</td></tr>{% endif %}
  {% if issuer.secondary_party %}<tr><th>Underlying strategy operator</th><td>{{ issuer.secondary_party }} ({{ issuer.secondary_role }})</td></tr>{% endif %}
  <tr><th>Asset description</th>      <td>{{ asset.description }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Amount</th>                 <td class="amount">{{ asset.amount_human }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>USD value at time of theft</th><td class="amount">USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</td></tr>
  {% if asset.usd_value_current %}
  <tr><th>USD value (current estimate)</th><td class="amount">USD {{ asset.usd_value_current }}</td></tr>
  {% endif %}
  {% if issuer.kyc_required %}
  <tr><th>KYC requirement at acquisition</th><td>Yes — {{ issuer.short_name }} required full identity verification{% if issuer.kyc_minimum %} with minimum subscription of {{ issuer.kyc_minimum }}{% endif %}</td></tr>
  {% endif %}
</table>

{% if issuer_freezable %}
<h2>4.1 Recoverable Positions under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s Authority</h2>
<p>
  After tracing through the perpetrator's on-chain forwarding,
  the following {{ issuer_freezable.total_count }}
  {{ "wallet holds" if issuer_freezable.total_count == 1 else "wallets hold" }}
  recoverable {{ issuer_freezable.token }} positions issued by
  {{ issuer.name }}. Each address is independently verifiable on
  Etherscan and was confirmed at the timestamp shown in the footer.
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="width:5em;">Status</th>
      <th>Address</th>
      <th class="amount" style="width:11em;">Balance</th>
      <th class="amount" style="width:9em;">USD value</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for h in issuer_freezable.holdings %}
    <tr>
      <td>
        {% if h.status == 'FREEZABLE' %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#2F6B3E;">FREEZABLE</span>
        {% else %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#7C2D12;">INVESTIGATE</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
      <td class="mono"><a href="{{ h.explorer_url }}">{{ h.address }}</a></td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ h.amount }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ h.usd }}</td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
<p class="small">
  <strong>FREEZABLE</strong> positions are
  ({{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }} addresses,
  {{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }} total) confirmed-held
  in wallets that have no matching KYC subscription on file with
  {{ issuer.short_name }} — they were received via direct on-chain
  transfer, not via subscription. These are the highest-priority
  targets for an immediate preservation request.
  {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
  <strong>INVESTIGATE</strong> positions
  ({{ issuer_freezable.investigate_count }} addresses,
  representing additional funds in
  {{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_suspected }} cumulative
  including freezable) require KYC verification at
  {{ issuer.short_name }} before status can be confirmed.
  {% endif %}
  Freeze capability assessment: <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.freeze_capability }}</strong>.
</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>5. Identified Wallets</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Address</th>
    <th>Role</th>
    <th>Type</th>
    <th>Notes</th>
  </tr>
  {% for w in identified_wallets %}
  <tr class="{{ w.row_class }}">
    <td class="mono"><a href="{{ w.explorer_url }}">{{ w.address }}</a></td>
    <td>{{ w.role }}</td>
    <td>{{ w.type }}</td>
    <td>{{ w.notes }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>

<h2>6. Recommended Actions</h2>

<h3>Immediate</h3>
<ol>
  <li>
    {% if issuer_freezable %}
    Issue a preservation request to {{ issuer.name }}
    ({{ issuer.contact_email }}) covering the
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} positions enumerated in section 4.1.
    As issuer of {{ issuer_freezable.token }}, {{ issuer.short_name }}
    holds protocol-level authority over those balances and is the
    only party in a position to technically halt redemption. A
    request originating from your office is materially more
    enforceable than a third-party request. The
    {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }}
    <strong>FREEZABLE</strong>
    {{ "address" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "addresses" }}
    ({{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }} total) are the
    primary targets;
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
    the {{ issuer_freezable.investigate_count }}
    <strong>INVESTIGATE</strong> addresses additionally warrant a
    KYC review request as part of the same preservation effort.
    {% endif %}
    {% if issuer.kyc_required %}
    {{ issuer.short_name }} required full KYC at the original
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} subscription path; they hold
    identifying information for the original subscribers on file.
    {% endif %}
    {% else %}
    Issue a preservation request to {{ issuer.name }}
    ({{ issuer.contact_email }}). As issuer, {{ issuer.short_name }}
    holds protocol-level authority over redemption and is the only party
    in a position to technically halt the {{ asset.amount_human }}
    {{ asset.symbol }} position at
    <a class="mono" href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">{{ current_holder.address }}</a>. A request
    originating from your office is materially more enforceable than a
    third-party request.
    {% if issuer.kyc_required %}
    {{ issuer.short_name }} required full KYC at original subscription;
    they hold identifying information for {{ victim.name }} on file.
    {% endif %}
    {% endif %}
  </li>
  {% if issuer.secondary_party %}
  <li>
    Copy {{ issuer.secondary_party }}, who manages the underlying
    {{ issuer.secondary_role }} the wrapper represents. They are the
    secondary route if {{ issuer.short_name }}'s freeze mechanism is
    unavailable or contested.
  </li>
  {% endif %}
  <li>
    Confirm chain-of-custody preservation of this evidence package and
    any linked case files. Per-transaction raw chain state at the time
    of fetch is retained on our side and available on request.
  </li>
</ol>

<h3>Investigative (over the following 1–2 weeks)</h3>
<ol>
  {% if issuer_freezable %}
  <li>Issue legal process to {{ issuer.short_name }} for KYC records on
      any party attempting to redeem or transfer
      {{ issuer_freezable.token }} from any of the
      {{ issuer_freezable.total_count }} addresses listed in
      section 4.1.
      {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
      Where {{ issuer.short_name }}'s KYC records confirm a third-party
      subscriber for an INVESTIGATE address, that address can be
      promoted to FREEZABLE and added to the preservation request.
      {% endif %}
  </li>
  {% else %}
  <li>Issue legal process to {{ issuer.short_name }} for KYC records on
      any party attempting to redeem or transfer the position out of
      <a class="mono" href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">{{ current_holder.address }}</a>.</li>
  {% endif %}
  <li>Issue legal process to any centralized exchange that receives
      onward transfers from the identified perpetrator wallets listed
      in Section 5.</li>
  {% if issuer.jurisdiction %}
  <li>Coordinate with the financial-supervisory authority in
      {{ issuer.jurisdiction }} regarding the issuer's obligations to
      cooperate with the freeze.</li>
  {% endif %}
</ol>

<h2>7. Service Providers Involved</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Service</th><th>Role</th><th>Why relevant</th><th>Suggested contact</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>{{ issuer.name }}</td>
    {% if issuer_freezable %}
    <td>Issuer of {{ issuer_freezable.token }} (recoverable positions held under their authority)</td>
    <td>Protocol-level control over {{ issuer_freezable.token }} redemption at the addresses in section 4.1; primary freeze target</td>
    {% else %}
    <td>Issuer of stolen {{ asset.symbol }} wrapper token</td>
    <td>Has protocol-level control over redemption; primary freeze target</td>
    {% endif %}
    <td>{{ issuer.contact_email }} (request escalation to compliance)</td>
  </tr>
  {% if issuer.secondary_party %}
  <tr>
    <td>{{ issuer.secondary_party }}</td>
    <td>{{ issuer.secondary_role|capitalize }}</td>
    <td>Controls underlying strategy; secondary freeze route</td>
    <td>(public compliance channel)</td>
  </tr>
  {% endif %}
</table>

<h2>8. Verification</h2>
<p>
  Every fact in this package is drawn from public Ethereum mainnet state
  and is independently verifiable. Each transaction listed in the timeline
  links to its Etherscan record. For each transaction we retain, on file:
  the raw transaction object, receipt, block header, fetch timestamp, and
  direct verification link.
</p>
<p class="small">
  Sources: Etherscan API v2 (transaction history); CoinGecko (historical
  pricing); our internal label database for entity attribution.
</p>

<h2>9. Investigator Attestation</h2>
<div class="signature-block">
  <p>
    I prepared this package on behalf of {{ victim.name }} from public
    Ethereum mainnet data fetched between {{ trace_started_at }} and
    {{ generated_at }} UTC. The transaction hashes, addresses, timestamps,
    and amounts set out in this brief are accurate to the best of my
    knowledge and were independently verified at the time of fetch.
  </p>
  <div class="signature-line"></div>
  <div class="signature-fields">
    <strong>{{ investigator.name }}</strong> · {{ investigator.organization }}<br/>
    Date: __________________________
  </div>
</div>


<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>{{ brief_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Strictly Confidential.</span> Intended only for the receiving agency.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
